text: Phyllis Winifred McQuaid (born March 6, 1928) is an American politician in the state of Minnesota. She served in the Minnesota Senate from 1983 to 1990 as an Independent Republican member, representing district 44. McQuaid previously served as mayor of St. Louis Park, Minnesota from 1978 to 1982. ==References== Category:1928 births Category:Living people Category:Minnesota Republicans Category:Women mayors of places in Minnesota Category:Women state legislators in Minnesota Category:Members of the Minnesota House of Representatives
